Clifford Snow

Clifford is described as an Addicted Mapper for the past three years since he started contributing to OSM. He is a member of OSM's Future Work Group, hosts OpenStreetMap-Seattle Meetup Group and helped with the importing of Seattle building outlines and addresses into OSM. His prior endeavors include glassblowing, managing an art center facility and telecom management.

Twitter Facebook Google+ Github

Duplicate addresses in Seattle

It was pointed out that Seattle has a number of duplicate addresses in OSM. Running a query in overpass convinced me that there were more than anticipated.

The overpass query run on overpass-turbo.eu

 1     <osm-script output="json" timeout="900" element-limit="1073741824">
 2       <id-query {{nominatimArea:Seattle}} into="area"/>
 3       <!-- gather results -->
 4       <union>
 5         <query type="node">
 6           <has-kv k="addr:housenumber" />
 7           <has-kv k="addr:city" v="Seattle" />
 8           <!-- <has-kv k="source" v="King County GIS" /> -->
 9           <area-query from="area"/>
10         </query>
11       </union>
12       <!-- print results -->
13       <print mode="body"/>
14       <recurse type="down"/>
15       <print mode="skeleton" order="quadtile"/>
16     </osm-script>

Some duplicates can easily be fixed by removing the duplicate. However, King County lables many buildings with the same address, such as mobile home parks. These need a add:unit tag added.

If you want to help, the list below has duplicates. Open up JOSM, then click on an item in the list.

Clifford Snow

Clifford is described as an Addicted Mapper for the past three years since he started contributing to OSM. He is a member of OSM's Future Work Group, hosts OpenStreetMap-Seattle Meetup Group and helped with the importing of Seattle building outlines and addresses into OSM. His prior endeavors include glassblowing, managing an art center facility and telecom management.
